SYNOPSIS
        varargs void channel_msg(string sMsg, string sChannel, int iMinLevel,
          int *aiWrapSettings, mixed xInfo, object *aoExclude,
          status tRemote, status tNoHist)

DESCRIPTION
        Sends a message sMsg to channel sChannel that users at least
        level iMinLevel will receive.
        sMsg: The message to the channel. "\n" will be added to the end.
        sChannel: The channel the message will be broadcast to. The default
          channel is "shout".
        iMinLevel: The minimum level a user has to be to hear the message.
          It will default to 1 if no arg is given.
        aiWrapSettings: An array used by break_string to handle wrapping
          the message over multiple lines. Default is ({ 75, 5, 1 }).
        xInfo: A mixed variable that will either resolve to this_player()
          or an array of Users. It is used to resolve if the sender is
          invis, an APP, their cap_name and real_name. In most cases
          you would send 0 as the default arg.
        aoExclude: an object array of users to exclude from hearing
          the message.
        tRemote: Should the message be sent to the other port (ie from
          dev to live or live to dev). Only certain channels allow for
          this setting, mostly wiz channels.
        tNoHist: If 1, the message won't show up in the channel's history.
